Detailed Description

This interface defines the access to the parameters of a WAP connection (WAP profile). Detailed information on the parameters can be found in the WAP forum document WAP-183-ProvCont-20010724-a, Version 24-July-2001, "Wireless Application Protocol, Provisioning Content".

Class WapProfile basically encapsulates the logical characteristics needed for a WAP request (as defined in PXLOGICAL), and it has a reference to an instance of class DataConnProfile in the form of an index.

The underlying concept is that a WAP profile has

  • logical WAP proxy parameters,
  • 0 or more sets of authorization parameters,
  • 0 or more sets of logical port parameters,
  • 1 or more sets of physical parameters, which are all accessed through a single flat interface, thus simplyfying the use of the interface.

The methods are grouped into logical, authorization, port and physical parameter set methods, set handling methods and general management methods. Each "setter" method is immediately followed by the corresponding "getter" method to enhance readability.
